      • FrameConfig

        public FrameConfig(@StringRes
                   int name,
                   @DrawableRes
                   int drawableId,
                   @DrawableRes
                   int frameId,
                   @Nullable
                   AspectConfigInterface aspectConfig,
                   int groupId)
        Creates a Frame Config
        Parameters:
        name - name of this frame
        drawableId - preview icon resource
        frameId - the frame image resource
        aspectConfig - the aspect that enable this frame.
        groupId - the group number to identifier a equal frame with different aspect. If the crop aspect changed the unfitting frame are replaced with a frame that fit the aspect and has the same group id.

      • FrameConfig

        public FrameConfig(@StringRes
                   int name,
                   @DrawableRes
                   int drawableId,
                   @DrawableRes
                   int frameId,
                   @DrawableRes
                   int frameMaskId,
                   @Nullable
                   AspectConfigInterface aspectConfig,
                   int groupId)
        Creates a Frame Config
        Parameters:
        name - name of this frame
        drawableId - preview icon resource
        frameId - the frame image resource
        frameMaskId - the mask of this frame as a blank and white image, full black are 100% transparent full white are opaque. this is Usefull for use JPEG's frames.
        !!! NOTE: if, your mask is an PNG image, you need to saveImage it as an 24bit or 32bit png and add an extra pixel line with rainbow colors, this is because Android itself has an bug !!!
        aspectConfig - the aspect that enable this frame.
        groupId - the group number to identifier a equal frame with different aspect. If the crop aspect changed the unfitting frame are replaced with a frame that fit the aspect and has the same group id.
